```suggestion
`f =O[ð“Ÿ s Ã—Ë¢ l] fun (i, x) â†¦ g x` as expressing that `f i` is `O(g)` uniformly on `s`.
```

I guess I don't really understand the restriction to principal filters here. For example, a slight modification yields:
```lean
/-- If `f = O(g)` eventually with respect to `l' Ã—Ë¢ s`, then `f_i = O(g)` eventually in `l'`. -/
theorem foo {l' : Filter Î¹} (h : f =O[l' Ã—Ë¢ l] (g âˆ˜ Prod.snd)) :
    âˆ€á¶  i in l', (fun x â†¦ f (i, x)) =O[l] g := by
  obtain âŸ¨C, hCâŸ© := h.bound
  obtain âŸ¨t, htl, htâŸ© := hC.exists_mem
  obtain âŸ¨u, hu, v, hv, huvâŸ© := Filter.mem_prod_iff.mp htl
  filter_upwards [hu] with i hi
  refine isBigO_iff.mpr âŸ¨C, Filter.eventually_iff_exists_mem.mpr âŸ¨v, hv, ?_âŸ©âŸ©
  exact fun y hy â†¦ ht _ <| huv âŸ¨hi, hyâŸ©
```
from which you can get:
```lean
/-- If f = O(g) uniformly on `s`, then f_i = O(g) for any `i âˆˆ s`.` -/
theorem isBigO_of_isBigOUniformly (h : f =O[ð“Ÿ s Ã—Ë¢ l] (g âˆ˜ Prod.snd)) {i : Î¹} (hi : i âˆˆ s) :
    (fun x â†¦ f (i, x)) =O[l] g := by
  revert i
  rw [â† eventually_principal]
  simpa using foo h
```
Yeah, this PR wasn't in the right generality, so I've reworked it.

Can you name a bunch of these results accorinding to the suggestion [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention/near/447491526) making things `protected` as appropriate?
```suggestion
theorem IsLittleO.const_id_atTop [LinearOrder F''] [NoMaxOrder F''] [ClosedIciTopology F'']
```

```suggestion
/-- Let `f : X x Y â†’ Z`. If as `y` tends to `l`, `f(x, y) = O(g(y))` uniformly on `s : Set X`
of finite measure, then f is eventually (as `y` tends to `l`) integrable along `s`. -/
```

```suggestion
/-- Let `f : X x Y â†’ Z`. If as `y` tends to `l`, `f(x, y) = O(g(y))` uniformly on `s : Set X`
of finite measure, then the integral of `f` along `s` is `O(g(y))`. -/
```
